==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''hlah-'', which might have come from an unattested Proto-Indo-European imitative root *''[[klak-]]''. Cognates include Old Saxon *''hlahhian'', Old High German ''hlahhan'', Old Norse ''[[hlæja]]'' and Gothic ''[[hlahjan]]''.
===Verb===
'''hlihhan''' (also ''hlæhhan'' and ''hliehhan'')

# to [[laugh]]

